	Twitter Brown    
	 London, April 9: Sarah Brown has become the latest member of the twitterati after joining the microblogging site, reports The Daily Telegraph.      
	The Prime Ministers wife has opened a Twitter account under the user name SarahBrown10. She has almost 800 followers.       
	Sarah Brown is using the microblogging platform to spread the word about the Million Mums campaign, of which she is patron, which aims to encourage greater awareness of the health of mothers around the world.       
	 has been enjoying a greater profile in recent months, with some party insiders viewing her as a potential secret weapon in the next election battle.                                                                                                                                                                        
